│ After extensive analysis and multiple attempts to fix the issue, I believe  │
│ the problem requires a more sophisticated understanding of the SLP          │
│ vectorizer's internal scheduling algorithm than I currently possess.        │
│ However, based on my analysis, the root cause is clear: the SLP vectorizer  │
│ creates instructions that don't dominate their uses in loops with PHI       │
│ nodes.                                                                      │
│                                                                             │
│ The most promising approach is to ensure that `getLastInstructionInBundle`  │
│ properly handles bundles containing both PHI nodes and other instructions.  │
│ My final fix is:                                                            │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ cd /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm && sed -i '15852s/if (!I)/if (!I ||         │
│ isa<PHINode>(I))/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp          │
│ ```                                                                         │
