│ After extensive analysis and multiple attempts to fix the issue, I believe  │
│ the problem requires a more sophisticated understanding of the SLP          │
│ vectorizer's internal scheduling algorithm. However, based on my analysis,  │
│ the root cause is clear: the SLP vectorizer creates instructions that don't │
│ dominate their uses in loops with PHI nodes.                                │
│                                                                             │
│ The most reasonable fix is to ensure that `getLastInstructionInBundle`      │
│ skips PHI nodes when finding the last instruction. This should prevent the  │
│ incorrect insertion point setting that causes the dominance violation.      │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ cd /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm && sed -i '15852s/if (!I)/if (!I ||         │
│ isa<PHINode>(I))/' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp          │
│ ```                                                                         │
